In muc.lists.linux-kernel, you wrote:
>Hi!
>In Linux-2.2, I have a problem while configuring multiple address to an 
>Interface. If i add the second address, it overwrites the existing one.
The current nettools don't support that for IPv4(the kernel does). Workaround:
either use the way described in Documentation/networking/alias.txt or
use iproute2 from ftp.inr.ac.ru:/ip-routing/
